00:22:14.919 --> 00:22:18.110
score so what this thing does is it says

00:22:18.120 --> 00:22:21.750
that uh when you sample a new point so

00:22:21.760 --> 00:22:23.669
you're trying to run a new experiment

00:22:23.679 --> 00:22:26.990
you grab a point from the parito front

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:30.390
and then you uh you expand around that

00:22:30.400 --> 00:22:32.269
normally so you take a normal random

00:22:32.279 --> 00:22:35.029
sample around this Paro

00:22:35.039 --> 00:22:37.510
point but then what they do on top of

00:22:37.520 --> 00:22:40.950
this is they down weight points that are

00:22:40.960 --> 00:22:45.190
far from the parito sample so they have

00:22:45.200 --> 00:22:46.630
this probabilistic function that

00:22:46.640 --> 00:22:48.110
prevents you from going too far away

00:22:48.120 --> 00:22:49.549
from your parito

00:22:49.559 --> 00:22:52.310
